						               													<description>Slappy Hands is a fun and unique dexterity game.  Each person has a &amp;ldquo;sticky hand&amp;rdquo;.  The hand is a small rubber hand that has a sticky film on it attached to a cord (actually all one piece of rubber).  A chip is placed in the middle of the table with the participants sitting on each side of the table.  Once someone says go, you try to grab the chip from the table with your sticky hand.  Once a chip is plucked from the table, that person scores one point and another chip is placed and it starts again.  Normally, the winner is the first to five points.  Certain chips can be worth two points adding extra incentive in grabbing that chip.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- from co-designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
